latestPosts.caption:
@blisssalonlansing 🇺🇸 this speaks to us. 🤭

Stylists, what are some ways you kill time when you finish a client early? Let us know in the comments. 👇

You’re going to want  to save this blonde placement. 📝

@laurakimhair 🇬🇧 states “I  wanted to create intentional dimension and be sure not to over foil, so following my effortless blonde placement will ensure you leave enough negative space. Tipping out will give that bolder blonde focal point around the face and ends.”

Want to recreate this gorgeous blonde on your clients? Laura used Flash Lift for a powerful, clean, even lift and glossed to perfection with the 🆕 Shades EQ Pearl Vinyl Collection.

The #RedkenRecipe:
💙 Lift: Flash Lift 8 Bonder Inside + Pro-oxide Cream Developer 20 Vol + 30 Vol
🩷 Zone 1: Shades EQ 06NB (15 g) + 🆕 08NP (10 g)
🩷 Zones 2 + 3: SEQ 🆕 010NP (10 g) + 🆕 010NV (10 g) + 000 (20 g)
🖤 Style: Naked Gloss Oil + One United
🖤 Finish: Spray Wax

latestPosts.caption:
Achieve a luminous, lived-in bronde with precision.🩷 ​

Follow along & enjoy these tips from #RedkenPartner @hairbylisamatthews 🇺🇸: ​
▪️Apply Zone 1 color starting in the front & drag the color down the further back you go to add depth, then brush through to blend​
▪️ Use a foil to avoid color transfer when clipping up hair for lowlight sections​
▪️ Keep lowlight placement on Zone 2 while feathering the ends to maintain a diffused look​

The 🆕 Shades EQ NP family delivers neutral results with natural reflect + advanced dye calibration for balanced, natural-looking blondes without over-toning. ✨ ​

The #RedkenRecipe: ​
🩷 Lowlights: Shades EQ 06N + 07G + 07NW (1:1:1) 06N + 0.5 oz 07G + 0.5 oz 07NW ​
🩷 Zone 1: #ShadesEQ 07N + 06N + 06NB (1:1:1) ​
🩷 Gloss:  SEQ 🆕 08NP + 🆕 010NP (1:1)

From subtle enhancements to dramatic transformations, Shades EQ is your secret weapon for creating stunning blondes. 🩷​

Explore the endless possibilities and join the #SEQ1001BlondesChallenge. ​

#130 by @victoria.doeshair 🇺🇸​
🩷 Global Gloss: Shades EQ 010N (1 oz) + 010P (.5 oz) + 010GRo (.6 oz)​

#131 by @stephenwilliamhair 🇬🇧 ​
Step 1:​
💙 Lift: Flash Lift Bonder Inside + Pro-oxide Cream Developer 10 Vol​
🩷 Lowlight: 09GB (30 g) + 07GB (30 g) + 09AA (1 cap full)​
🩷 Zone 1: 07GB ​
🩷 Zone 2: 010WG (20 g) + 09GB (20 g) + 09AA (20 g)​
Step 2:​
🩷 Hairline: 07GB + 09AA​
🩷 Global Gloss: 010WG + 09AA + dash of 08GI​

#132 by ​@bombshellsbyalyssa 🇺🇸
🩷 Global Gloss: 09N (.5 oz) + 09VG (1 oz) + 010T (.5oz) + 000 (.5 oz)

#133 by @tinted.by.taylor 🇺🇸 ​
🩷 Zone 1: 08N ​

latestPosts.caption:
Understanding a Shades EQ chart = knowing your gloss inside and out. 🙌​

From cool to warm and everything in between, @blakereedevans breaks down how the background + tone is key to nailing your gloss game consistently. ✨ ​

🖤 Black to gray background = cool​
🤎 Brown to tan background = natural + balanced​
🩷 No background = pure vibrancy ​

Don’t forget to save this SEQ lithochart breakdown for your next gloss consult. 🔖

Wow-worthy color AND visibly reversed damage in just ONE use?* ✨ #ShadesEQ does it all (with your expert touch, of course).

With the widest demi-permanent palette in the world*, the shade options are endless. 

What Shades EQ shade are reaching for?
#RedkenBrandAmbassador @sarabotsfordhair’s 🇺🇸 #RedkenRecipe:​
🩷 Zone 1: #ShadesEQ 05N + 06GI​
🩷 Zone 2: #SEQ 07M + 08GRo​
🩷 Zone 3: 09M + 010GRo​

*Based on Kline 2024 Professional Hair Color Market
